{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a square baking tin (20 cm) with baking paper.","Place teabags in a large bowl then place bowl on mixing bowl lid. Weigh in coconut, cherries and boiling water. Remove bowl and gently mix together with spatula then set aside.","Place ginger and apricots in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to bowl with tea.","Place biscuits in mixing bowl and crush <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a separate bowl and set aside.","Place chocolate and golden syrup in mixing bowl then melt <b>5 min\/50°C\/speed <b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt again <b>5 min\/50°C\/speed <b>. Remove tea bags from large bowl and discard.","Add pecan nuts, reserved crushed biscuits and reserved tea-soaked mixture then stir <b>20 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Spoon into prepared tin and level surface then place in fridge for at least 2 hours or until set.","Cut into squares and serve with chai tea."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 chai teabags","50 g desiccated coconut","150 g glacé cherries","200 g water, boiling","50 g crystallised ginger, in pieces","100 g dried apricots","150 g digestive biscuits, quartered","200 g dark chocolate, 70% cocoa, small pieces or callets","50 g golden syrup","50 g pecan nuts"]}],"id":"r111356","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/--XWCPHwHyXA\/XZWd2ed2ujI\/AAAAAAAAerA\/CWY9Wqrx5tclgUTPXL53x0lX61SlD33rgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_NECmHoyjl5G3KrUh.png","title":"Masala Cherry Tiffin","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.8 g","fat":"12.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"37.7 g","calories":"1163 kJ \/ 278 kcal"},"usefulItems":"square baking tin (20 cm), baking paper, large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Although ‘tiffin’ has now become strongly associated with the British practice of teatime treats, like the chocolate-based refrigerator cake, it is actually an Indian-English word for a light snack. In this recipe it is both – a slightly spiced, chilled, mouth-watering chocolate snack which can be enjoyed with masala chai or coffee!"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 30m","12 portions"]}